<body>
    <h1>Rules of Multiplication - Example</h1>

    <div class="content">
        <h2>Given Data</h2>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Age</th>
                    <th>Bachelor's degree only</th>
                    <th>Master's degree</th>
                    <th>Total</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Under 30</td>
                    <td>90</td>
                    <td>10</td>
                    <td>100</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>30-40</td>
                    <td>20</td>
                    <td>30</td>
                    <td>50</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Over 40</td>
                    <td>40</td>
                    <td>10</td>
                    <td>50</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Total</th>
                    <th>150</th>
                    <th>50</th>
                    <th>200</th>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Questions</h2>

        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Probability that the engineer has a Master's degree:</strong>
                <div class="formula">P(Master's degree) = Total with Master's degree / Total engineers = 50 / 200 = 0.25</div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Probability of Master's degree and age between 30-40:</strong>
                <div class="formula">P(Master's degree and 30-40) = Engineers with Master's degree and age 30-40 / Total engineers = 30 / 200 = 0.15</div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Probability of Master's degree or age over 40:</strong>
                <div class="formula">
                    Using the formula: P(A ∪ B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A ∩ B)<br>
                    P(Master's degree) = 50 / 200<br>
                    P(Age over 40) = 50 / 200<br>
                    P(Master's degree and age over 40) = 10 / 200<br><br>
                    P(Master's degree or age over 40) = (50 / 200) + (50 / 200) - (10 / 200) = 90 / 200 = 0.45
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Probability of Master's degree given that he is over 40:</strong>
                <div class="formula">
                    Using conditional probability: P(A|B) = P(A ∩ B) / P(B)<br>
                    P(Master's degree and age over 40) = 10 / 200<br>
                    P(Age over 40) = 50 / 200<br><br>
                    P(Master's degree | Age over 40) = (10 / 200) / (50 / 200) = 10 / 50 = 0.2
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
